The paper deals with deep learning algorithms for image restoration, specifically for hyperspectral image processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of CNNs, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of 3D-convolutional networks, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper deals with image processing, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper mentions the use of intrinsic properties of a CNN without any training, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
